definition: echinoderm, the phylum containing sea urchins, sea cucumbers etc
(of sth) to move/to set in movement/to displace/to touch/to make use of/to stir (emotions)/to alter/abbr. for 動詞|动词[dong4 ci2], verb

sentences.english: The echinodermata are furnished with remarkable organs .
sentences.chinese: 棘皮動物具有一種引人注意的器官。

sentences.english: But echinoderms apparently deliver more carbon to the sediments than do forams, for example.
sentences.chinese: 舉例來說，棘皮動物傳送到海底的碳明顯比有孔蟲多。

sentences.english: These small, spiny echinoderms are found in oceans all over the world.
sentences.chinese: 這些小的，多刺的棘皮動物能夠找到在全世界的海洋。
